What did you do about the really pitted parts, or did you have any? I
can't see just grinding them all down because the sheet metal would get 
I wire brush the pits to clean them out, then fill them in with 
oxyacetylene 
and MIG wire. 
another great tool is the 3M trico wheels on a power tool I like the 6S
or 7S wheels... probably have to get these from a hardware wholesaler. I
got mine from L.A. Benson in Baltimore, they do mail order. 
